MBAZWANA
cops in the Umhlabuyalingana Local Municipality are investigating a case of
murder. This after
the body of 13-year-old Thobani Khambule, who was beheaded, was found in the
bushes in Mtanenkosi. Thobani’s
body was found partially burnt after he was last seen on Saturday, 28 May. Cops Police
spokeswoman Lieutenant-Colonel Nqobile Gwala said officers worked around the
clock to identify and arrest the perpetrator. “A
29-year-old man was taken in for questioning after police received reports that
he was last seen with the victim. Following this development, police proceeded
to an old, abandoned house, where the head of the victim was found in a pit
toilet,” Gwala said. She added
that the bush knife used during the killing was also found. “The motive
for the killing remains unclear, and investigations continue. The suspect will
appear before the Mbazwana Periodical Court on 1 June, on a charge of murder,”
Gwala said.